userdoc.notice: Layer-2 Rollup Simulation (Advanced / Recruiter-Level) ------------------------------------------------------ Optimistic rollup-style L1 contract that:  - Escrows ETH/ERC20 deposits  - Lets a Sequencer submit batches (txDataHash + newStateRoot + withdrawalRoot)  - Has a challenge window for optimistic finality  - Supports disputes via an external FraudProofVerifier  - Allows withdrawals after finalization using Merkle proofs

Layer-2 Rollup Simulation (Advanced / Recruiter-Level)
 ------------------------------------------------------
 Optimistic rollup-style L1 contract that:
  - Escrows ETH/ERC20 deposits
  - Lets a Sequencer submit batches (txDataHash + newStateRoot + withdrawalRoot)
  - Has a challenge window for optimistic finality
  - Supports disputes via an external FraudProofVerifier
  - Allows withdrawals after finalization using Merkle proofs

IMPORTANT:
 This verifies a Merkle proof using ordered pairs:
 computed = keccak256(computed || sibling) for each proof element.
 Off-chain you must build the proof in the same way.
